OL,3,CShoplifting - Who's Paying the Price?
OL,5,FBrowns Department Store is not alone
OL,6,Fin facing these pressures. In Catford,
OL,7,FSouth East London, convenience store
OL,8,Fowner Kaual has invested thousands in
OL,9,Fextra CCTV, security tags, and
OL,10,Felectronic stickers for common items
OL,11,Fdue to shoplifting. Kaual says his
OL,12,Fstaff must weigh the risk of
OL,13,Fintervening and facing potentially
OL,14,Fviolent individuals, calling the
OL,15,Fpolice, or letting offenders leave.
OL,16,FAfter feeling frustrated at the
OL,17,Fpolice's response to shoplifting
OL,18,Fincidents, he worries how long the 40-
OL,19,Fyear old family business can last.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
