OL,3,CShoplifting - Who's Paying the Price?
OL,5,FDespite the challenges facing
OL,6,Fretailers and shopworkers, there is
OL,7,Fgrowing momentum behind efforts to
OL,8,Fturn the tide. The Metropolitan Police
OL,9,Frecently carried out the UK's largest
OL,10,Fever crackdown on organised
OL,11,Fshoplifting gangs. The Met told
OL,12,FTonight it "understands shoplifting
OL,13,Fcauses fear, misery and suffering to
OL,14,Fretail workers and communities". It
OL,15,Fsays "it is increasing patrols and
OL,16,Fworking closely with retailers, and
OL,17,Fofficers are already solving double
OL,18,Fthe number of shoplifting offences
OL,19,Fcompared to this time last year."
